summary: How Nick Fury Will Lose His Eye.  Ok so we already know that 1.  "The last time I trusted someone, I lost an eye." 2. He's gonna...
body:
How Nick Fury Will Lose His Eye.

Ok so we already know that 1. “The last time I trusted someone, I lost an eye.” 2. He’s gonna lose his eye during Captain Marvel. And while everyone else is thinking, “Oh he’ll trust a Skrull in disguise, and then he’ll lose his eye.” I on the other hand have a hilarious alternative. Nick Fury trusts Goose the Cat. Hear me out. In Captain Marvel #1 Rocket tries to kill the cat because he recognizes it as a Flerken Cat. Very Dangerous. I believe Nick will trust the Flerken cat and the cat will attack him and rip his eye out. The Skrull theory is more probable but c,mon, it would be hilarious if the reason he doesn’t trust easy is because of A CAT.

summary: Yo so do you know exactly what makes Carol Danvers so powerful?
question: Yo so do you know exactly what makes Carol Danvers so powerful?
answer:
her hair? haha

but if it’s an honest question, I checked the wiki again because you made me realize I kinda forgot / didn’t really know how to answer! Because It’s kinda all over the place, since she’s a character that has been changed so much over many years. I think the only solid answer we’re gonna get, is what the movie gives us.

In general, I think it’s because she’s meant to reflect the powers of a white hole. Which according to Marvel logic means…  control over stellar energies, (so also HEAT) and the electromagnetic spectrum and gravity. (which is why she can fly I think.) But it has a lot to do with her fusing with the powers of Mar Vell during an explosion… since he’s Kree, and the Kree are insanely powerful I think.

in the movie I don’t even know if Mar Vell is present. And I think it’s just gonna be “the Kree experimented on her and fused her with Kree powers,” and it turns out making someone part Kree AND part human makes them like, incredibly powerful, since humans are ridiculously sturdy creatures. Or, maybe giving her extra crazy powers was just part of the experiments.

I think she’ll be nerfed in the MCU, because everybody is. And even if she’s nerfed from her comicbook levels, I’d still totally buy that she could be the strongest hero in the MCU (if they go in that direction), because her comic powers are… well just look at the wiki:

“Carol Danvers initially possessed superhuman strength, endurance, stamina, flight, physical durability, a limited precognitive “sixth sense”, and a perfectly amalgamated human/Kree physiology that rendered her resistant to most toxins and poisons … Light speed travel and the ability to survive in the vacuum of space were also possible … absorb energy and project it in photonic form … While she lacks a constant source of energy to maintain the abilities at their previous cosmic level, she can temporarily assume her Binary form if empowered with a high enough infusion of energy. … Danvers has superhuman strength and durability, can fly at roughly six times the speed of sound … retains her sixth sense, and can discharge explosive blasts of radiant energy, which she fires from her fingertips. She also demonstrates the ability to absorb other forms of energy, such as electricity, to further magnify her strength and energy projection, up to the force of an exploding nuclear weapon. When sufficiently augmented, she can withstand the pressure from a 92-ton weight, and strike with a similar level of force, although Hank Pym theorized that this likely was not her limit. “

Christ.

I mean, MOST Marvel heroes are also way more powerful in the comics than in the films, since they need to make things more comprehendable and palpable for a mainstream audience. So I think she’ll be just above Thor/Doctor Strange/Hulk/Scarlet Witch (the big guns) in the MCU. Maybe Thor will be more STURDY than her. (meaning like, defensively: how much damage you can take.) since he took the full blast of a supernova in Infinity War. But she’ll likely be stronger offensively: i.e. the ability to CHANNEL the power of a supernova.

lol you got me on a nerd rant again GOOD JOB<3
